(:summary    "Small hack to insert a custom signature"
 :created    "1999"
 :updated    "1999"
 :license    "GPL-2"
 :authors    (("Benjamin Drieu" . "drieu@alpha10.bocal.cs.univ-paris8.fr"))
 :maintainer ("Benjamin Drieu" . "drieu@alpha10.bocal.cs.univ-paris8.fr")
 :provided   (signature)
 :keywords   ("mail")
 :homepage   "http://www.grassouille.org/emacs/index.en.html"
 :commentary "\
signature.el inserts random signatures at the end of a mail.
Signatures are picked randomly from a file in the directory
$HOME/`signature-directory'/

Matching is performed against all the keys of the variable
`signature-email-addresses-alist' (from which the name of the file
is taken).  As soon as a match is correct, 

$Id$")
